* parameter file is strictly prohibited.


* This file contains transport parameters at 300 K for SiliconGermanium
* under biaxial compressive strain present when a thin SiGe film is grown
* on top of a relaxed Silicon substrate as occuring in the base of
* npn-SiGe HBTs (heterobipolar transistors).
* The electron parameters refer to the out-of-plane direction
* (i.e. perpendicular to the SiGe/Si interface) and the hole parameters
* to the in-plane direction (i.e. parallel to the SiGe/Si interface)
*
* The transport parameters have been obtained from the full-band 
* Monte Carlo simulations in
*
* `Full-Band Monte Carlo Simulation of Electrons and Holes
*  in Strained Si and SiGe' by F. M. Bufler, 1998
*  ISBN 3-89675-270-7
* 
* Herbert Utz Verlag
* Zieblandstr. 7
* D-80799 Muenchen
* Germany
* phone: +49-89-277791-00
* fax:   +49-89-277791-01
* e-mail: utz@utzverlag.com
* URL:    http://www.utzverlag.com  
* 
* The band gap in relaxed SiGe alloys have been extracted from the
* measurements in
*
* R. Braunstein, A. R. Moore and F. Herman, 
* "Intrinsic Optical Absorption in Germanium--Silicon Alloys",
* Phys. Rev. 109, pp. 695-710, 1958
*
* and the values in strained SiGe calculated according to the
* model solid theory of C. G. Van de Walle.
*
* Consistent limiting values for Silicon (and PolySi) are also
* provided.

Material = "SiliconGermanium" {

Auger * coefficients:
{ * R_Auger = ( C_n n + C_p p ) ( n p - ni_eff^2)
  * with C_n,p = (A + B (T/T0) + C (T/T0)^2) (1 + H exp(-{n,p}/N0))
	A	= 6.7000e-32 ,	7.2000e-32	# [cm^6/s]
	B	= 2.4500e-31 ,	4.5000e-33	# [cm^6/s]
	C	= -2.2000e-32 ,	2.6300e-32	# [cm^6/s]
	H	= 3.46667 ,	8.25688	# [1]
	N0	= 1.0000e+18 ,	1.0000e+18	# [cm^(-3)]
}


Scharfetter * relation and trap level for SRH recombination:
{ * tau = taumin + ( taumax - taumin ) / ( 1 + ( N/Nref )^gamma)
  * tau(T) = tau * ( (T/300)^Talpha )          (TempDep)
  * tau(T) = tau * exp( Tcoeff * ((T/300)-1) ) (ExpTempDep)
	taumin	= 0.0000e+00 ,	0.0000e+00	# [s]
	taumax	= 1.0000e-05 ,	3.0000e-06	# [s]
	Nref	= 1.0000e+16 ,	1.0000e+16	# [cm^(-3)]
	gamma	= 1 ,	1	# [1]
	Talpha	= -1.5000e+00 ,	-1.5000e+00	# [1]
	Tcoeff	= 2.55 ,	2.55	# [1]
	Etrap	= 0.0000e+00	# [eV]
}

